Here is a working Pine Script for a simple Moving Average Crossover strategy.

This script uses two Simple Moving Averages (SMA): a fast one and a slow one. When the fast SMA crosses above the slow SMA, it generates a "Buy" signal, and when it crosses below, it generates a "Sell" signal.

```pinescript
//@version=5
strategy("SMA Crossover Strategy", shorttitle="SMA Cross", overlay=true)

// --- Inputs ---
// Define the lengths for the fast and slow moving averages
fastLength = input.integer(10, title="Fast SMA Length")
slowLength = input.integer(30, title="Slow SMA Length")

// --- Calculations ---
// Calculate the Simple Moving Averages
fastMA = ta.sma(close, fastLength)
slowMA = ta.sma(close, slowLength)

// --- Crossover Conditions ---
// Determine when the fast MA crosses above the slow MA (Buy Signal)
buyCondition = ta.crossover(fastMA, slowMA)

// Determine when the fast MA crosses below the slow MA (Sell Signal)
sellCondition = ta.crossunder(fastMA, slowMA)

// --- Strategy Execution ---
// Enter long position when the buy condition is true
if buyCondition
    strategy.entry("Long", strategy.long)

// Exit long position (or enter short if you prefer a full reversal) when the sell condition is true
if sellCondition
    strategy.entry("Short", strategy.short) // For a simple crossover strategy, this acts as an exit from the long or entry to a short position.

// --- Plotting for Visualization ---
// Plot the MAs on the chart
plot(fastMA, color=color.blue, title="Fast SMA")
plot(slowMA, color=color.red, title="Slow SMA")
```

